South Africa’s Business Unity Body Names Majokweni New CEO, Chamber Says

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-08-04T13:14:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/south-africa-s-business-unity-body-names-majokweni-new-ceo-chamber-says.html
Business Unity  South Africa  named
Nomaxabiso Majokweni as chief executive officer, said Neren Rau
of the country’s chamber of commerce.  “Her challenge will be to reunite BUSA, to bring back”
the Black Management Forum, Rau, the chief executive officer of
the South African Chamber of Commerce and Industry, said in an
interview in Johannesburg today. The chamber if a member of the
business unity group.  The Black Management Forum withdrew from BUSA, the main
lobby group representing companies in South Africa, last month
because it said its voice is being suppressed.  Majokweni, who headed up management of the Sandton
Convention Center, will take office on Sept. 1, according to the
South African Press Association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
